Princess Dagmar of Denmark and her fiance Tsar Alexander III

Princess Dagmar of Denmark, later Empress Maria Feodorovna of Russia (1847-1928), sister of Queen Alexandra and mother of Tsar Nicholas II, with Tsar Alexander III (then the Tsarevich) shortly after their engagement in 1866. Mary Evans Picture Library makes available wonderful images created for people to enjoy over the centuries. © Mary Evans Picture Library/CHARLOTTE ZEEPVAT

Media ID 14349398
